Method behavioural specifications:
- The integer array parameter `costs` must not be null.
- The length of the integer array parameter `costs` is greater than or equal to 1 and is less than or equal to 100000.
- All values in the integer array parameter `costs` are greater than or equal to 1 and are less than or equal to 100000.
- The integer parameters `k` and `candidates` are greater than or equal to 1 and are less than or equal to the length of the integer array parameter `costs`.
- The long result is the total cost to hire exactly `k` workers according to the specified rules.